//Benefits Page //Heading text A Gift With Six Factors Chaḷaṅgadānasutta Six factors of a religious donation: 1. Three factors of the donor
a. Before Donation: Good Mood\n b. Whilst donation: Feeling of confidence\n c. After donation: Feeling of upliftment
2. Three factors of the recipient
a. No greed (or practice in progress for freedom from greed)\n b. No hatred (or practice in progress for freedom from hatred)\n c. No Delusion (or practice in progress for freedom from delusion)
Benefits:
Beyond calculation, measurement, a great mass of merit.\n Simile: Grasp of whole of the water of the ocean
- Source: Aṅguttara Nikāya 6.37
